function separateDigits(nums) {
    const answer = [];
    for (const num of nums) {
        const digits = num.toString().split("").map(Number);
        answer.push(...digits);
    }
    return answer;
}
```


    For each number num in the nums array:

1. Convert the number to its string representation.
2. Iterate through the string and extract the digits, appending them to the answer array.

Repeat this process for all numbers in the nums array.

solutionCode.java:
    ```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public List<Integer> separateDigits(int[] nums) {
    List<Integer> answer = new ArrayList<>();
    for (int num : nums) {
        String numStr = Integer.toString(num);
        for (char ch : numStr.toCharArray()) {
            answer.add(Character.getNumericValue(ch));
        }
    }
    return answer;
}
```


    For each number num in the nums array:

1. Convert the number to its string representation.
2. Iterate through the string and extract the digits, appending them to the answer array.

Repeat this process for all numbers in the nums array.
